<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376949>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Croton carajasensis Sodré & Secco. A Flowering branch, B Detail of leaf base showing trichomes and nectaries, C Staminate flower, D Pistillate flower, E. Capsule, F Seed, ventral side. Drawn by Carlos Alvarez from J.L.C. Costa et al. 07 (A–C) and J.L.C. Costa et al. 23 (D–F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376949/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376951>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Field images of Croton carajasensis Sodré & Secco.A Flowering branch, B Flowering branch showing thyrses with staminate flowers, abaxial surface of leaves and detail of the yellow basilaminar nectary in the insert, C Flowering branch showing thyrses with pistillate and staminate flowers, D Flowering branch showing adaxial surface of leaves and thyrses with staminate flowers, E Thyrse with immature capsules and staminate flowers and buds, F Capsule and staminate flowers. Photographs by André Luiz de Rezende Cardoso." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376951/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376955>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Croton carajasensis Sodré & Secco sp. nov. On the left showing South America, the boundaries of Brazil (gray line), the limits of Pará state (black line), and the area of distribution of C. carajasensis (whitish rectangle), and on the right the detailed distribution of the species in Serra dos Carajás and surroundings." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376955/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

